Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.17,0:00:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}"Everyone must have someone\Nthey want to kill."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.21,0:00:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}l think this is what started it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.93,0:00:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}We wrote the names\Nof the people we want to kill{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.13,0:00:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}and showed each other secretly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.81,0:00:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}Right after that...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.61,0:00:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The name l wrote\Nwas Yutaro Yamagiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.13,0:00:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}People are murdered\None after another...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.04,0:00:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The name l wrote on my piece of\Npaper was Misato Akaike.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.40,0:00:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I wrote Yoshihiko Hakamada.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.70,0:00:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The name l wrote on the piece\Nof paper was Mrs. Kayo Kojima.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.80,0:00:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We should tell the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.64,0:00:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I won't be arrested, will l?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.74,0:00:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Make sure\Nyou don't tell other detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.05,0:00:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I won't kill just because\Nl got a threatening note.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.77,0:00:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Who did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.13,0:00:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm suspecting someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.45,0:00:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll try to get an answer myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.77,0:00:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}People are cornered, but still...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.97,0:00:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ukita?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.37,0:01:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}And the man whose name l wrote...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.13,0:01:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l've been doing lift maintenance\Nfor 20 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.77,0:01:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l guess this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.21,0:02:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.37,0:02:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"I really loved you,\Nbut the way l loved you was wrong."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.85,0:02:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"l'm sorry..."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.85,0:02:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Darn...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.85,0:02:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l don't want to die\Nwhen she still hates me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.22,0:02:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.10,0:02:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry, Jessie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.02,0:03:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It isn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.90,0:03:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Yes?\N- Sorry for coming so early.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.48,0:03:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please come to the police station\Nwith us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.80,0:03:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Shota...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.32,0:03:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:03:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.32,0:03:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He died.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.23,0:04:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.15,0:04:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Tokyo Metropolitan Police Hospital"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We did our best to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't worry about me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.91,0:04:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}it's okay to cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.27,0:04:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Hey, bring her with us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.11,0:04:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But that's her husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.17,0:05:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The woman could've killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry, but it's time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.51,0:05:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.91,0:05:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Nana...\N- l'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.71,0:05:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}A horrible wife\Nwho requested someone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.07,0:05:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}to kill the husband she divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.99,0:05:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Murder-swap, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.19,0:05:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Kill him for me\Nand l'll kill for you in return."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.83,0:05:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Murder-swap, please!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Your Turn to Kill"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Room 102, Kayo Kojima murdered\NRoom 201, Keisuke Ukita murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.20,0:06:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Victims fell down the lift\Nin Hikifune Warehouse
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.03,0:06:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Reinvestigation\Non property manager's suicide"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Series of murders\Nat Kuramae's condo"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.72,0:06:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}They are cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}All right, where should we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.88,0:06:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Maybe from whether we should\Ninvestigate it with Kuzumi's case?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Is his job related\Nto the crime scene in any way?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sir, Kuzumi works\Nat a lift maintenance company,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}he was responsible for the\Nmaintenance of the lift there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.71,0:07:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He could tamper with it\Nif he wanted to?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.87,0:07:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The security camera was broken,\Nso we don't know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.67,0:07:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}However, Kuzumi's toolbox\Nwas left at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.59,0:07:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}By the way,\NKuzumi's subordinate said
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.24,0:07:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}that he was pretty obsessed\Nwith lifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.64,0:07:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Obsessed with lifts!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He regularly fiddles with the lift\Nin the condo he lives in for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.80,0:07:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Dear me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.76,0:07:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He'd make the lift silent\Nwhen it arrives
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.32,0:07:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and says that\N"Angelina became modest."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.88,0:07:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What? He names the lifts?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.56,0:07:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I guess he didn't have any friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}For now, we can't verify whether\Nit was intentional or an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.27,0:07:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}In that case,\Nwe have to start with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Suspect, Nana Tezuka"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.23,0:07:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}ls Mr. Hosokawa her brother\Nor her husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He's still married\Nwith Nana, legally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.79,0:08:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I called him Big Bro\Nwithout knowing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.31,0:08:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Someone wrote on a forum\Nto ask for someone to kill Big Bro,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.71,0:08:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}so the police suspects\Nthat Nana wrote it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.91,0:08:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}And Nana is still in custody today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.52,0:08:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Someone murdered another person\Nand put Nana through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You borrowed someone's smartphone,\Nwrote you want a murder-swap,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.88,0:08:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and put Mr. Hosokawa's photo\Non the forum.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.84,0:08:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I told you, l--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}A week after the first message\Nwas written,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.16,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Hosokawa himself\Ncalled the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.08,0:08:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and without a doubt,\Nyou are the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.64,0:08:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}However, that evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Hosokawa was involved in a fall\Nwith your friend, Yuzuru Kuzumi,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and died there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:08:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I did not write that message.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.44,0:09:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Did Yuzuru Kuzumi read this message?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.24,0:09:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I already told you yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You've been separated for years
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.64,0:09:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}but he didn't agree\Nto get a divorce,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.04,0:09:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}so you wanted to murder him...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.40,0:09:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l've answered this question\Nmany times as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.88,0:09:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We were taught to ask\Nthe same questions again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.35,0:09:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.51,0:09:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Tell her why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.16,0:09:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Because if you are lying,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.92,0:09:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}we'll gradually see a hole in it\Nif we ask over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.32,0:09:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Is that the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.64,0:09:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}And? Have you found any hole\Nin what l've told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.15,0:09:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.15,0:09:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Then...\N- Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.91,0:09:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Do you know how many people\Nwho lived in your condo died?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.27,0:09:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Let us investigate it thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.31,0:09:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But it's the game...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.63,0:09:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}That's how tricky the case is,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.67,0:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}make sure you don't tell\Nanother detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.47,0:09:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm here because l want to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.67,0:09:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I did nothing suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.39,0:10:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.03,0:10:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You scared me!\Nl died for two seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Sorry, sir, but...\N- What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.27,0:10:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Is there any connection\Nbetween Mr. Kuzumi's accident
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.81,0:10:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and Mr. Ukita's death?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.36,0:10:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}By the way, who among these\Nthree people wrote Mr. Ukita's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.21,0:10:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Three people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.41,0:10:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.69,0:10:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}lf Mr. Ukita was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.41,0:10:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}that means among Mr. Tamiya,\NMiss Ono and the caretaker,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.81,0:10:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}one of them\Nwrote Mr. Ukita's name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.41,0:10:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.66,0:10:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Who do you think it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.22,0:10:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"301, Ono"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Caretaker, Tokoshima"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.26,0:10:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Tokoshima?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.58,0:10:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.42,0:10:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Among the three,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Tokoshima wasn't really\Non good terms with Mr. Ukita.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- I see.\N- No matter who wrote it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.42,0:10:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}the people who could've drawn\NMr. Ukita's piece of paper were...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:11:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Tamiya, Xinyi, Miss Ono,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.79,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mrs. Akaike and the caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.09,0:11:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}There are five people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.95,0:11:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But Mrs. Akaike and the caretaker\Nare dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.63,0:11:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}so the people who could've killed\NMr. Ukita are...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.88,0:11:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Tamiya...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.76,0:11:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Xinyi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.08,0:11:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and Miss Ono.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.89,0:11:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Miss Ono.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.53,0:11:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry for saying something\Nl shouldn't the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.17,0:11:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}When someone dumps me like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.93,0:11:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l'm scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.41,0:12:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It isn't enough as an apology,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}but this is a massage oil\Nmade with natural ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.61,0:12:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's good for your skin\Nand it makes you calm too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.78,0:12:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Oh, but you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l won't give you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.18,0:12:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If l give it to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.62,0:12:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}you will turn a cold shoulder\Nto me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.66,0:12:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No, Miss Ono--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.10,0:12:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}So l'll apply it on you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.58,0:12:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.10,0:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.58,0:12:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Don't bother...\N- Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.49,0:12:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.15,0:12:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He gave it to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.29,0:12:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}The caretaker made it himself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.61,0:12:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Were you and Mr. Tokoshima\Nclose friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.41,0:12:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We hadn't really spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.13,0:12:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What about Mr. Ukita?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.97,0:13:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.69,0:13:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Well, because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.17,0:13:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You suspect everything\Nwhen you're tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.43,0:13:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No, that's not what l mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.79,0:13:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Pressing on the acupressure points\Nmakes your body and mind relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.11,0:13:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Hey, are you sure?\N- Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.39,0:13:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We found the owner of the smartphone\Nused to write the forum's request,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.87,0:13:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}a man spoke to her\Nwhen she was jogging...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.75,0:13:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He cried and said it was urgent,\Nso l lent it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The characteristics of the man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.25,0:13:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He looked exactly like the man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You see,\Nthe man who just passed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.83,0:13:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Oh, Yoshihiko Hakamada!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.97,0:13:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- What?\N- The description of his outfit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.09,0:13:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}also matched Kuzumi's clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.97,0:14:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}So Kuzumi borrowed a phone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.77,0:14:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and wrote the request to kill\NMr. Hosokawa on the forum?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.69,0:14:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.01,0:14:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We don't know his motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.50,0:14:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I guess it's quicker\Nto wait for Kuzumi to wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.74,0:14:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Sumida Police Station"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.58,0:14:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I guess you've already realised.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.73,0:14:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I did not tell anyone\Nabout the murder-swap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.10,0:14:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.30,0:14:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You're investigating it alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.66,0:14:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes. l...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.30,0:14:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}lf you investigated properly,\NMr. Ukita...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.53,0:14:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and Mr. Hosokawa didn't have to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.73,0:14:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll talk to other detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.49,0:14:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.89,0:15:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}This is because...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.13,0:15:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}there's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.21,0:15:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Problem?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I hope didn't say anything\Nyou shouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.75,0:15:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Will you give me a break?\NWere you tailing me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.51,0:15:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm here just by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.31,0:15:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}This coincidence might happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.23,0:15:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I didn't tell her anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.47,0:15:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Then l won't say anything either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.66,0:16:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}lt hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.82,0:16:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.86,0:16:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Have you gotten used\Nto life in hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why did he go to hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.18,0:16:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He could've gone to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.74,0:16:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't drink during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Heaven, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He was nice to us,\Nbut in other people's eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.90,0:16:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}he was evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.38,0:17:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.98,0:17:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.90,0:17:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Ukita loved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.70,0:17:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I know, but bring him a fresh one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.66,0:17:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.94,0:17:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Ukita loved one that's soft
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.78,0:17:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}after being put in the fridge\Novernight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.50,0:17:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Who killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.54,0:17:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Penguin Moving Company"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.42,0:17:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}This is none of your business,\NMrs. lshizaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.34,0:17:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It is my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.10,0:17:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.02,0:17:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Because l want to run away too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.06,0:17:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.82,0:17:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ms. Kitagawa is going to move away!\NWhat do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.27,0:18:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What can l?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.43,0:18:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}She wants to run away alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.31,0:18:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We're all accomplices!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.19,0:18:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Excuse me, what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.97,0:18:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Please carry this outside.\N- Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.21,0:18:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- You...\N- Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Cut it out!\N- l won't let you escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.45,0:18:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Hey! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.25,0:18:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.55,0:18:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Who got the piece of paper\Nwith my name on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.85,0:18:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.45,0:18:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm going to be killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.77,0:18:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}And it's her fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If you're so worried,\Nwhy don't you move away too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.78,0:18:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I bought my flat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.58,0:18:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We have to pay the mortgage\Nfor 20 more years!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.85,0:18:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sell it, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.33,0:18:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}How can l sell it?\Nlt's a murderers' condo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.37,0:18:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- So this is the rumoured...\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.37,0:18:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}See? There's rumour going around\Nabout it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.58,0:19:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sora.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.98,0:19:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I think Sora fell from his scooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.82,0:19:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.78,0:19:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.08,0:19:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sora?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.52,0:19:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please wait for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.44,0:19:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.96,0:19:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.52,0:19:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Thank you.\N- No worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.92,0:19:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sora, come.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.60,0:19:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.17,0:19:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.72,0:19:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}When is this going to stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}As we told you the other day,\Nthe detective, Mr. Kamiya--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.92,0:19:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}ls that guy doing his job\Nproperly?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.04,0:19:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He won't tell us\Nthe results of the investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.84,0:19:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}maybe the police will suddenly catch\Nthe murderer tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.16,0:19:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, maybe, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Anyway, let's calm down, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.60,0:20:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.76,0:20:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Thanks for having me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.29,0:20:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.63,0:20:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Nana!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I would've gone to pick you up\Nif you had told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry, l was tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.75,0:20:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Then you should've called\Nall the more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.65,0:20:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I need the energy\Nto ask for help too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.16,0:20:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I was too tired\Nto ask for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.56,0:20:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.56,0:20:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What have you been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.76,0:20:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What did you do at Miss Ono's flat?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry... l was asking what name\NMiss Ono wrote and drew...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.12,0:20:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry,\Nplease don't talk about that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.48,0:20:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll go and lie down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.43,0:21:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry, l have to go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.91,0:21:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't worry about it, his relatives\Nwill probably be present.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.08,0:21:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.88,0:21:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Your eyes are swollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.63,0:21:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If this is for Nana,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.55,0:21:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l'll do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.28,0:22:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's none of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.96,0:22:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But it's what you saved
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.24,0:22:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}for your retirement...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.48,0:22:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Hello. l would like to talk\Nabout the name you wrote and drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Go back inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.12,0:22:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- I haven't finished--\N- l said, go back inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.24,0:22:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Are you doing what you did before?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.72,0:22:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}When will you stop nagging me\Nabout my last job?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.48,0:22:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You're the one who...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.04,0:22:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Drama is just a hobby, okay?\Nlt isn't your job--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.04,0:22:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Sorry about that.\N- lt's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.92,0:22:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}How can l help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.84,0:22:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- The name you wrote--\N- l don't want to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.48,0:22:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.48,0:22:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Because l've just found\Nmy life's purpose, that is, drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.56,0:22:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I don't want anything else\Nto take up my time. See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.16,0:22:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please don't go yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.88,0:22:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.55,0:22:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Knowing all the names is the answer\Nto solving the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.75,0:22:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.92,0:23:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I think it will let you concentrate\Non your life's purpose too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.23,0:23:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I don't get\Nwhy you assume this pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.31,0:23:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}This pose is tougher than kneeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.52,0:23:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and it shows how serious l am.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.56,0:23:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.68,0:23:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}People will laugh at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.44,0:23:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Do be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.48,0:23:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You're just like who l used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.04,0:23:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.08,0:23:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You have more passion than other\Npeople, but you go in the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.56,0:23:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You'll only\Nbring other people trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.16,0:23:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's fine if you only cause trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.76,0:23:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}but they'll ridicule you\Nas a workaholic,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.32,0:23:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}spread rumours about you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.88,0:23:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and eventually, you'll be cornered\Nand have to retire early...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.68,0:23:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l digressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.82,0:24:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Could you have written the name\Nof a former colleague?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.22,0:24:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.34,0:24:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It was my subordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.38,0:24:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I wrote the name of a man\Ncalled Takafumi Kono.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.90,0:24:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}On the paper l drew,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.58,0:24:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}the name written was Takafumi Kono,\Nin Hiragana.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.26,0:24:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I taught him\Nwith all the experience l had.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.42,0:24:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I was proud of this subordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.50,0:24:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Thank you for telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.30,0:24:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Also, on the piece of paper l drew,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.18,0:24:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}it says, "Someone who can't\Nsort rubbish properly."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.46,0:24:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.30,0:24:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I won't laugh at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.82,0:24:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Good luck with your search\Nfor the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.78,0:25:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Manager's office"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.34,0:25:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.30,0:25:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Room 304's Ms. Kitagawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.86,0:25:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}They moved away yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.34,0:25:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.90,0:25:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Do you know where they moved to?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.95,0:25:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I didn't ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.30,0:25:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.14,0:25:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But l can tell you\Nwhere she works.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.38,0:25:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.38,0:25:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.50,0:25:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll now reply to messages from our\Nlisteners. lt's Sumika Kitagawa's...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.58,0:25:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Oh, it's Grooving Jam\Nhosted by Ms. Kitagawa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.10,0:25:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}How do you know\Nsuch a local radio station?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.90,0:25:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why do you know, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.82,0:25:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I looked up data of everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.14,0:26:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ms. Kinoshita, you use\Nyour real name at work too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.66,0:26:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No, that isn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.46,0:26:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Oh, and...\N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.50,0:26:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You didn't wipe the earphone\Nbefore you put it in your ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.26,0:26:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It makes me fall in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.42,0:26:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The matter has gotten too serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.70,0:26:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We should keep a low profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.86,0:26:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll apologise for the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.66,0:26:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"It is your turn to kill"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.10,0:26:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l'll also forgive you for hacking\Ninto my computer at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.02,0:26:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.94,0:27:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}India is an lT superpower now,\Nisn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.58,0:27:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I am Bangladeshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.02,0:27:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The one who is familiar with lT\Nis the illegal immigrant here?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.58,0:27:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You really made all the threats?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.14,0:27:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What? You want to punch me?\NDo it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.42,0:27:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't actually punch me!\Nl'll call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.10,0:27:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You punched in a way\Ndifferent from Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.34,0:27:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Both of us will be in trouble\Nwith the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.54,0:27:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.42,0:27:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}tell me who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.62,0:27:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.23,0:27:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Was it Mr. and Mrs. Akaike?\NOr was it Yoshihiko Hakamada?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.01,0:27:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.86,0:27:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.72,0:28:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What was revealed about this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.64,0:28:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The murder was committed\Nby several people.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.92,0:28:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It must've come to a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.04,0:28:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yutaro Yamagiwa's head\Nstill hasn't been found.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.48,0:28:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm not in charge,\Nbut my stomach hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.88,0:28:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Reports about two cases\Ncaused a stir,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.84,0:28:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}that's why nobody pays attention\Nto ours and it helps a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.96,0:28:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If someone is arrested...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.92,0:28:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}people will pay attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.00,0:28:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}And they will come out at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.60,0:29:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Prepare yourself. We can't afford\Nto arrest the wrong person.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.12,0:29:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But we haven't made any progress\Non the cases of Mr. and Mrs. Akaike
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.24,0:29:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and Kayo Kojima,\Nwho is only a leg now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.24,0:29:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We'll be in trouble at this rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.60,0:29:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I got a report from the forensics\Nabout Ukita's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.80,0:29:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.88,0:29:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}They found something interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.36,0:29:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}about the footprint\Nleft at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.40,0:29:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry for asking you\Nto gather on a holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.72,0:29:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.44,0:29:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's okay, this is better\Nthan being alone at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.28,0:29:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, it makes me feel safer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.76,0:29:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Something is bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.67,0:29:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's unusual for people to write\Na name of someone they want to kill,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.71,0:29:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}did you do it as a prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.19,0:29:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No. Only a few people\Nactually wanted to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.89,0:29:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Everyone else was reluctant.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.17,0:29:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I probably stopped talking\Nhalfway through.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.97,0:29:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Someone might complain\Nif we didn't write a name,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.33,0:29:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}there was an awful tension\Nin the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.31,0:29:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.27,0:29:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}In the midst of it, isn't it weird\Nthat a piece of paper was blank?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.31,0:30:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If someone did this,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.03,0:30:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}someone might demand to know\Nwho didn't write a name down.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.03,0:30:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why didn't Ms. Kitagawa say
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.47,0:30:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}that the piece of paper was blank\Nand someone cheated at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.55,0:30:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Indeed.\NNow l'm curious after you said this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.43,0:30:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Isn't this curious?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.79,0:30:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.27,0:30:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Usually, footprints aren't left\Nat a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.75,0:30:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Maybe when the murderer strangled\NUkita with a piece of wire...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.96,0:30:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}they stepped on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.92,0:30:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}So this is the murderer's...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.63,0:30:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- How long is it?\N- 26.5 centimetres.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.60,0:30:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's an average shoe size for men.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.60,0:30:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If it's a woman, she is quite tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.64,0:30:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But that alone won't tell us much.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.52,0:30:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You want to say Ms. Kitagawa lied\Njust based on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.49,0:30:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Kuroshima said the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.05,0:30:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}that it was possible\Nthat some people among us lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.75,0:30:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, but l didn't mean Ms. Kitagawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.15,0:30:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}She could've prepared\Nthe blank paper afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.47,0:31:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}it also prevented her\Nfrom digging her own grave
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.59,0:31:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}by saying a false name\Nand being asked in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.19,0:31:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But it's just a thought, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.79,0:31:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Well, some people didn't give\Na specific name as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.11,0:31:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and l suspect all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.84,0:31:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.52,0:31:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"People who\Ndon't give up their seat..."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.64,0:31:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"402, Enomoto"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.96,0:31:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}And Oda Nobunaga as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.96,0:31:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}And "Someone who can't\Nsort rubbish properly."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.64,0:31:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l asked Mr. Tamiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.92,0:31:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The name he wrote\Nwas Takafumi Kono.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.99,0:31:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Is it...\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.15,0:31:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}And on the piece of paper he drew,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.83,0:31:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}it says, "Someone who can't\Nsort rubbish properly."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.01,0:31:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}ln other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.29,0:31:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ms. Kitagawa, Mr. Tamiya,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.14,0:31:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Kuroshima and l lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.49,0:31:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Is that what you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.33,0:31:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, this is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.65,0:31:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.57,0:32:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll talk about this\Nfrom a different angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.29,0:32:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}For now, people whom we don't know\Nwhat name they wrote are...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.05,0:32:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Miss Ono and the caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.11,0:32:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The names that we don't know\Nwere drawn by whom
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.15,0:32:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}were Mr. Ukita and the caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.91,0:32:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.91,0:32:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The names written by Miss Ono\Nand the caretaker
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.37,0:32:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}were either Mr. Ukita\Nor the caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.53,0:32:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.61,0:32:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But l think it's unlikely\Nfor the caretaker
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.33,0:32:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}to write his own name,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.33,0:32:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}so Miss Ono wrote the caretaker
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.37,0:32:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and the caretaker wrote Mr. Ukita.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.69,0:32:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.61,0:32:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}now we have filled\Nthe "name written" column.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.15,0:32:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Nobody wrote what was written on\Nthe pieces of paper you two drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.32,0:32:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.36,0:32:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wait, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.36,0:33:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ms. Kitagawa and Mr. Tamiya too...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.28,0:33:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}So l want to ask\Nthe two of you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.60,0:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I know you have alibis of when\Nmurders happened in our condo,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.88,0:33:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}but in Mr. Ukita's case...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.32,0:33:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What did you do on that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.64,0:33:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't suddenly\Ntreat us like suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.08,0:33:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.32,0:33:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But when l was organising the facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.64,0:33:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l found that it is also\Na possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.04,0:33:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's just a possibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.28,0:33:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}but Ukita could've been involved\Nin the gangsters' fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.88,0:33:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But the gang that Ukita belonged to\Ndidn't function as an organisation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.89,0:33:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I've checked people whom Ukita knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.43,0:33:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He used to steal produce\Nfrom farms and orchards
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.15,0:33:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and put them on black market,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.67,0:33:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}then he'd gain the margin\Nof the sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.03,0:33:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It was quite cheap as a thug's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.07,0:33:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He hasn't been paying\Nhis flat's rent either.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.55,0:33:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What bothers me\Nis Mr. and Mrs. Akaike's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.09,0:33:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.13,0:33:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}They didn't live in luxury,\Nbut they were pretty rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.81,0:34:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Also, Ukita had no alibi on the\Nnight the Akaike couple were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.88,0:34:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Ukita and the other two killed\NMr. and Mrs. Akaike for money,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.88,0:34:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}they had a fight when dividing\Nthe money and Ukita was killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.20,0:34:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If that's the case,\Nthe people who killed Ukita...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.08,0:34:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}were these two?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.20,0:34:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I think one of the four people here\Nkilled Mr. Ukita.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.96,0:34:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Enomoto, Kuroshima,\NTamiya, Kitagawa"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.24,0:34:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}This mostly hit the bull's eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.42,0:34:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wait, Shota.\NWhat about Mrs. lshizaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.26,0:34:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The name, Yoshimura,\Nwhich Mrs. lshizaki said she drew,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.62,0:34:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}wasn't written by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.02,0:34:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But Mrs. lshizaki wrote her own name
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.26,0:34:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and she's scared\Nthat she'll be killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.54,0:34:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}so l don't think she lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.27,0:34:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.58,0:34:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, somebody lied\Nabout what name they wrote as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.82,0:34:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If Mrs. lshizaki wrote her own name,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.62,0:34:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}then the caretaker\Ncould have written himself too.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.86,0:35:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Who would use an honorific\Nwhen writing their own name?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.10,0:35:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It is a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.18,0:35:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's rude to suspect the ladies\Nwhen we aren't exactly sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.62,0:35:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Well, l threw away\Nthe piece of paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.70,0:35:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}so l don't know how to prove\Nthat l didn't lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.70,0:35:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But the names written\Nby the caretaker and Mrs. Akaike
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.70,0:35:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}are only a deduction, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.14,0:35:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.82,0:35:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Look, we don't know the names here\Nfor sure too.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.26,0:35:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, about Miss Ono.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.66,0:35:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I made a desperate effort to ask,\Nbut she didn't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.74,0:35:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}See? There are too many holes\Nin the deduction, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.98,0:35:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.86,0:35:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I thought l hit the bull's eye...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.58,0:35:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l'm sorry/ l'll deduce this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.70,0:35:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If everything will be solved\Nin the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.94,0:36:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l don't mind being suspected at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.70,0:36:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Okay. l might suspect\Nthe two of you again...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.82,0:36:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}because l want to protect Nana.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.26,0:36:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.58,0:36:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Frankly, l get overwhelmed easily,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.90,0:36:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and l think there will be times\Nthat l can only see Nana,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.74,0:36:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}so l'm really sorry,\Nplease forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.66,0:36:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.98,0:36:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sanae and Kuroshima\Nmust be secretly angry with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.75,0:36:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Of course, l know you are too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.75,0:36:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I think they are angry
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.55,0:36:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and l think they're hurt\Nbecause you suspected them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.69,0:36:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.77,0:36:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}However...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.33,0:36:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l don't know if l should speak\Nfor Sanae too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.53,0:36:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.73,0:36:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I couldn't say it\Nbecause l was afraid to.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.29,0:36:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The detective told me\Nsomething unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.13,0:36:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What? You couldn't say anything back\Nafter he said that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.93,0:36:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What should l have said back?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.09,0:37:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It is true that l lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.21,0:37:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't say you lied.\NThat wasn't a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.53,0:37:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.73,0:37:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What we also do, we do out of love!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.05,0:37:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If they find out\Nthe various things about us...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.05,0:37:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}it'll make our family seem\Nlike we haven't got as much love
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.71,0:37:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}as that couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.63,0:37:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's frustrating!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.55,0:37:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.79,0:37:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Am l wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.69,0:37:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You are right!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.89,0:37:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fscx343\fscy397}It happened\Nwhen he was in middle school.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.03,0:37:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}So l said l'd go talk\Nto another detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.31,0:37:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Problem?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.31,0:37:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I can't tell you the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.07,0:37:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}but l found out a certain fact\Nabout the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.29,0:37:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}However, l concluded\Nthat investigating the case alone
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.01,0:37:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}is the shortcut\Nto solving the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.29,0:37:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.33,0:37:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}This meeting between you and me...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.61,0:38:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}keep it a secret from Mr. Enomoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.65,0:38:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He keeps it a secret\Nfrom Sanae's husband too?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.93,0:38:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But we talked to them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.81,0:38:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He just repeated
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.17,0:38:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}that he couldn't tell me\Nmore about the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.54,0:38:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He found a clue,\Nbut couldn't tell Mr. Enomoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.78,0:38:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}That's what l've been thinking too.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.66,0:38:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Enomoto was in the caretaker's\Noffice at that time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.38,0:38:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He didn't participate in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.10,0:38:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If he was doing something...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.58,0:38:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He did it for Sanae.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.22,0:38:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I don't want to think that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.15,0:38:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l think we should check out Sanae\Nas well.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.19,0:38:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.59,0:38:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.83,0:38:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Just let the police\Ntake care of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.23,0:38:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But we can't count on them!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.03,0:38:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Shota.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.99,0:38:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.03,0:38:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.23,0:39:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Tamiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.31,0:39:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Could it be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.13,0:39:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"TK Queen"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.09,0:39:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Very fine, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.21,0:39:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.35,0:39:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But this place is closed, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.03,0:39:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.11,0:39:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I thought you were going to treat us\Nto lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.91,0:39:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll treat you to something,\Nbut it isn't food.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.79,0:39:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It's this lounge!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.87,0:39:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.89,0:39:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We'll rent it\Nas our drama group's practise room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.47,0:39:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Look, although it's small,\Nthere is a stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.38,0:39:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We can even perform a short play.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.94,0:39:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}My seniors,\Nyou are all pretty talented,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.94,0:39:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}if you have a place\Nwhere you can concentrate,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.62,0:39:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}you can go a step further.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.50,0:39:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Oh, this is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.71,0:39:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We aren't a professional drama group
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.93,0:39:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and we only do what we enjoy\Nwhen we aren't working, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.27,0:40:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You can aim to be pro now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.63,0:40:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}The direction we go\Nshould be a group decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.69,0:40:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm running out of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.25,0:40:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.69,0:40:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Anyway, l will pay\Nthe whole sum of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.29,0:40:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Are we happy with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.85,0:40:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.37,0:40:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Nana!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.29,0:40:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You're late! You should've called.\Nl was worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.53,0:40:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry. But l found the bank\Nwhere Mr. Tamiya worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.97,0:40:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.49,0:40:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I tried to ask Mrs. Tamiya casually.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.89,0:40:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}You said we would\Nlet the police do their job.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.17,0:40:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But l meant Sanae's part.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.65,0:40:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.49,0:40:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No, l think we shouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.17,0:40:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.21,0:40:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We should see\Nwhat Takafumi Kono is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.61,0:40:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What will you do after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.13,0:40:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Tell him what's going on\Nand tell him to be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.23,0:41:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What can you tell him\Nabout the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.37,0:41:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.45,0:41:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But l want to protect him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.85,0:41:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I don't want what happened\Nto Big Bro happen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.73,0:41:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Anyway, let's just meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.89,0:41:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.29,0:41:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Thank you very much for talking\Nto us about getting a loan.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.19,0:41:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Let's begin...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.75,0:41:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Well...\N- Please ask anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.51,0:41:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry for being rude, but would you\Nlet Mr. Kono be in charge of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.59,0:41:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Kono?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.15,0:41:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, Mr. Kono helped my friend\Non getting a loan,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.47,0:41:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}we heard that he was very helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.19,0:41:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'm very sorry, but nobody\Nin our branch is called Kono.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.77,0:41:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}If he was transferred\Nto another branch,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.09,0:41:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}and we have to check\Nall the bank's branches...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.62,0:41:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Orangutan Time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.10,0:42:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.38,0:42:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}There was something different\Nabout the man just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.37,0:42:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What is it? l give up. Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.45,0:42:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He's the only one\Nwho's not wearing a name tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.73,0:42:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Please ask me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.78,0:42:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Oh, did he forget to?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.72,0:42:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Excuse me,\Nis Mr. Takafumi Kono here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.52,0:42:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Kono?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.80,0:42:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Let me see... Oh, he's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.28,0:42:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.32,0:42:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.40,0:42:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Should l call him here?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.12,0:42:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No. Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.32,0:42:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}That's too much!\Nl can't finish it within today!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.12,0:42:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- It's easy for you.\N- Will you do it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.40,0:42:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Good luck.\N- All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.32,0:42:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.48,0:42:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Kono, l presume?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.96,0:43:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wow... Seriously?\NYou're so annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.84,0:43:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Are you going to attack me here?\NThe security guard is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.88,0:43:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I think you've got the wrong idea.\NWe're Mr. Tamiya's...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.72,0:43:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}That man told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.84,0:43:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What is it? l will be killed?\NBe careful when l go home at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.48,0:43:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He even gave me a book\Non self-defence. lt's annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.28,0:43:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We won't attack you.\Nlt's the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.96,0:43:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Yes, we want to see\Nthat you're safe--
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.20,0:43:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l don't care at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.08,0:43:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I have nothing to do with that guy\Nin the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.40,0:43:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But Mr. Tamiya said you were\Na subordinate he was proud of.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.77,0:43:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I do the exact opposite\Nof what he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.41,0:43:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He is too serious,\Ntoo honest, and too hard-working.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.19,0:43:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}What is wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.03,0:43:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Despite that,\Nhis performance was only average.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.51,0:43:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}It was too inefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.85,0:43:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Inefficient?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.13,0:43:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Anyway,\Ndon't drag me into your troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.95,0:44:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Tamiya said Kono\Nwas a subordinate he was proud of,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.12,0:44:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}but he wrote Kono's name.\Nl think l can understand why.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.88,0:44:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Somehow it's frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.88,0:44:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I won't laugh at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.96,0:44:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Good luck with your search\Nfor the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.36,0:44:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}But still, we should tell him\Nto be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.72,0:44:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}I'll go and say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.28,0:44:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Shota!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.16,0:44:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.76,0:44:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l'm sorry! Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.40,0:44:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Wait, where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.40,0:44:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Kono, please listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.12,0:45:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Don't actually attack me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.36,0:45:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.28,0:45:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Mr. Kono!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.40,0:45:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}- Mr. Kono!\N- Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.00,0:45:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Call an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.92,0:45:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}We should call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.72,0:45:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}He must've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.96,0:45:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Hey, he did it, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.11,0:45:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"Your Turn to Kill"
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.03,0:45:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l would like to declare\Nthat the game is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.10,0:45:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}Totally innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.02,0:45:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}There is something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.54,0:45:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}That means Sanae killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.35,0:46:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}"What is Room 402's secret?"
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.43,0:46:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}l hope your suspicions are wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.47,0:46:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx343\fscy397}No!
